'''''Chaos and Disorder,''''' released in 1996 by [[Prince (artist)|Prince]] (his stage name at that time being [[File:Prince logo.svg|12px]]), was his final album of new material for [[Warner Bros. Records|Warner Bros]], and was therefore produced as a collection of leftovers only put on record to fulfill contractual obligations. ''Chaos and Disorder'' was one of Prince's least commercially successful releases and met mixed reviews upon release. Some reviewers commented that had it not been a Prince release, it would have been met with much wider approval.{{Citation needed|date=December 2009}} The album reached #26 in the US and #14 in the UK, and is now out of print.

'''''Chaos and Disorder,''''' released in 1996 by [[Prince (artist)|Prince]] (his stage name at that time being the love symbol he created), was his final album of new material for [[Warner Bros. Records|Warner Bros]], and was therefore produced as a collection of leftovers only put on record to fulfill contractual obligations. ''Chaos and Disorder'' was one of Prince's least commercially successful releases and met mixed reviews upon release. Some reviewers commented that had it not been a Prince release, it would have been met with much wider approval.{{Citation needed|date=December 2009}} The album reached #26 in the US and #14 in the UK, and is now out of print.
